        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Hardened malformed plugin/tool/schema metadata boundaries so hostile or unreadable synthetic plugin data is quarantined, omitted, diagnosed, or treated as absent instead of crashing provider routing, runtime tool resolution, Gateway/MCP catalogs, Codex prompt/report paths, plugin SDK helpers, bundle MCP catalog projection/materialization, and related assistant startup surfaces.\n- Kept fixtures synthetic: tests and notes use names like `fuzzplugin`, `mockplugin`, `mockplugin_status`, and `fuzz_move_*`, not the reported third-party plugin name.\n- Latest update carries Codex dynamic-tool descriptor snapshots through bridge construction/execution, avoids repeated fragile `name`/`description`/`parameters`/`execute`/`prepareArguments` reads, preserves before-tool source metadata for code-mode policy classification, and quarantines unreadable argument preparers before execution.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nNo linked closing issue.\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nNo linked related issue.\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nMaintainer-directed hardening/debugging work.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: malformed runtime plugin tool schemas and hostile plugin/config/provider/manifest/native-approval/outbound-action/bundle-MCP/Codex dynamic-tool metadata can crash, widen decisions, or bypass schema quarantine before normal OpenClaw diagnostics, setup, provider routing, gateway startup planning, Gateway catalog rendering, MCP loopback handling, approval forwarding, manifest/capability auth gating, provider payload conversion, prompt-cache setup, Codex reporting/instruction generation, plugin SDK normalization, agent-core tool lookup, cached plugin descriptor execution, static plugin tool registration, bundled capability runtime capture, bundle MCP catalog projection, bundle MCP catalog materialization, or Codex dynamic-tool bridge setup completes.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`, local focused lint/format checks, local autoreview, synthetic/private-name scrub, and AWS Crabbox Linux `pnpm check:changed` plus a clean-main baseline probe for the failing unrelated extension-test lane. Blacksmith Testbox was unavailable in this shell because `blacksmith auth login` is required.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- Force-pushed branch head `384ea21e93fa86b7a7d3b6fc1f080a3d4a0e2eea`.\n- Focused Codex bridge proof: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/codex/src/app-server/dynamic-tools.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- Focused before-tool metadata proof: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.integration.e2e.test.ts -t \"preserves code-mode metadata when wrapping with a descriptor snapshot\" --reporter=verbose`\n- Format/lint/diff checks: `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/codex/src/app-server/dynamic-tools.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/dynamic-tools.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.integration.e2e.test.ts`, `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/dynamic-tools.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/dynamic-tools.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.integration.e2e.test.ts`, and `git diff --check`.\n- Local review: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- AWS Crabbox changed gate on branch head `384ea21e93`: `CRABBOX_AWS_REGION=us-east-1 CRABBOX_CAPACITY_REGIONS=us-east-1,us-east-2,us-west-2,eu-west-1,eu-central-1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws --shell -- \"corepack pnpm check:changed\"`\n- AWS Crabbox clean-main baseline for the exact failing lane on `origin/main` `d9db23dc2f`: `corepack pnpm exec tsgo -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental false`\n- Changed-file scrub for the reported plugin name and private path patterns.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- Focused Codex bridge proof passed: 1 file, 41 tests passed.\n- Focused before-tool metadata proof passed: 1 passed, 19 skipped.\n- Format, targeted oxlint, and `git diff --check` passed.\n- Autoreview initially found three real regressions; all were fixed. Final autoreview was clean with no accepted/actionable findings.\n- AWS Crabbox `check:changed` provider `aws`, lease `cbx_f7608dd17f33`, run `run_f339d828630a`, passed guards plus core/core-test/extensions typecheck, then failed only `typecheck extension tests` on `extensions/googlechat/src/targets.test.ts` and `extensions/matrix/src/matrix/sdk/transport.test.ts`.\n- Clean `origin/main` baseline provider `aws`, lease `cbx_e1bb459f62ba`, run `run_bcbead0e747c`, reproduced the exact same `googlechat`/`matrix` extension-test type errors, so the broad gate failure is unrelated main drift.\n- Current branch diff and PR body scrub pass for the reported plugin name and private paths.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- Synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures with unreadable names, schemas, descriptions, approval fields, provider metadata, MCP catalog fields, cached runtime descriptors, and Codex dynamic-tool descriptors no longer crash the relevant projection/resolution paths.\n- Healthy siblings, such as `mockplugin_status`, continue through materialization, descriptor caching, provider payload conversion, MCP/Gateway listing, agent-core validation, and Codex dynamic-tool bridge registration while malformed siblings are omitted, quarantined, or diagnosed.\n- Codex dynamic tools no longer reread fragile descriptor getters after projection, unreadable argument preparers fail closed before execution, and before-tool hook classification still sees source-tool metadata for code-mode policy handling.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Blacksmith Testbox `pnpm check:changed` was not run because `blacksmith` is not authenticated in this shell.\n- AWS Crabbox `check:changed` did not finish green because latest `origin/main` already fails `test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json` in unrelated `googlechat`/`matrix` tests; a clean-main Crabbox baseline reproduced those exact errors.\n- GitHub CI for the newest force-push is still running/pending.\n- No live third-party plugin was referenced or exercised; tests intentionally use synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- PR remains draft while this fuzzing/hardening lane continues.\n- Latest pushed commit: `384ea21e93fa86b7a7d3b6fc1f080a3d4a0e2eea` (`fix(codex): carry dynamic tool descriptors`).\n",
